bamtools
------------------------------------------
BamTools provides both a programmer's API and an end-user's toolkit for
handling BAM files.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.1.0-1
  libbamtools2.4.0-2.4.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-4.9.3-1
  libjsoncpp1-1.0.0-1bl1
  libstdc++6-4.9.3-1
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-2
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.20.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.3-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/pezmaster31/bamtools

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/pezmaster31/bamtools/archive/v2.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bamtools-2.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bamtools-2.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bamtools-2.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bamtools-2.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbamtools2.4.0-2.4.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbamtools-devel-2.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bamtools)
  /usr/bin/bamtools
  /usr/bin/bamtools-2.4.0.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bamtools.README
  /usr/share/doc/bamtools/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bamtools/README

(libbamtools2.4.0)
  /usr/bin/cygbamtools-2.4.0.dll

(libbamtools-devel)
  /usr/include/bamtools/api/BamAlgorithms.h
